A LITTLE BIT OF THIS YEAR|2023

lately, I've been manifesting everything... CHEERS to an amazing year!✨️

October was magical. My husband surprised me with a trip for our 5th anniversary to Vermont. 😍 

So freakiinnnn thankful.

2023 thank you! ✨️
2024✨️ manifesting peace, love, and health for everyone! 💗✨️ 

GOAL: to consistency post here... maybe relaunch my shop or close it.

✨️Hello 2024!✨️
Trying to create a reel was so difficult. I took me a minute to refresh my memory. Today was an awesome day. I had my colleagues create a video walking into 2024 with all positive vibes. I'll post on my story later. 

I should be heading to my portable to turn on the heater, but instead, I'm working in the library looking over some students' data and looking forward to accomplishing their learning goals. 

This year, I'll be posting more of my daily routine and activities you might find helpful to use in ELA.

#teacher #teachinggoals #2024goals

✨️Day 1✨️
It was a very relaxing day at work. We shared so many good strategies during PD. I made a fun video with the staff that I promise to share in my story after posting this. 

I've a feeling this semester is going to go by so fast. I need to start planning my summer vacation. ✌️✨️🏖

TEACHER ALERT! 🚩
It might be funny to many. But we teachers know the struggle. When I was in the classroom. I remember constantly bothering my partners for a restroom break. Thankfully, they all were very understanding about it.🫶🏼 

🚺🚾Holding in the need to go to the restroom constantly can have negative effects on your overall health. 

🚽Urinary Tract Infections (UTIs): When you hold your urine for extended periods, it gives bacteria more time to multiply in the urinary tract, increasing the risk of developing a UTI.

🥼Bladder Issues: Holding in urine frequently can weaken the bladder muscles over time, leading to a decreased bladder capacity and potentially causing issues like urinary retention or incontinence.

🚑Kidney Problems: Holding in urine can put pressure on the kidneys, which can affect their functioning and potentially contribute to the formation of kidney stones.

🏨Overstretching of the Bladder: Consistently ignoring the urge to urinate may cause the bladder to overstretch, leading to decreased sensitivity and potentially resulting in difficulties in emptying the bladder completely.

😔Discomfort and Pain: Holding in urine for too long can cause discomfort, pain, and even cramping in the lower abdomen.

🧠🤯 Impact on Focus and Productivity: Frequent urges to go to the restroom can be distracting, affecting your ability to concentrate and negatively impact productivity.

👂It is generally advised to listen to your body's signals and use the restroom when needed, rather than holding it in for extended periods.
